# Manual API requests (IntelliJ HTTP client / VS Code "REST Client").
# Get a token first:  TOKEN=$(scripts/dev-token.sh)  then paste it below.
# Guest (anonymous) token:  scripts/dev-token.sh --guest  -> paste as guestToken.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@token = paste-access-token-here
@guestToken = paste-guest-token-here

### Health — public, no auth
GET {{host}}/actuator/health

### Me — requires a valid Bearer token (expect 200 + your userId/email)
GET {{host}}/api/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Me without a token — expect 401
GET {{host}}/api/me

### Me with a garbage token — expect 401
GET {{host}}/api/me
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-jwt

### Search the exercise catalog by name (global + mine)
GET {{host}}/api/exercises?name=press
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create my own exercise — expect 201 (repeat: 409 duplicate name)
POST {{host}}/api/exercises
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Cable Crossover",
  "category": "push",
  "measurementType": "WEIGHT_REPS"
}

### Create an exercise as a GUEST — expect 403 (members only)
POST {{host}}/api/exercises
Authorization: Bearer {{guestToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Guest Move",
  "measurementType": "BODYWEIGHT"
}
